@paulstef @SarahLouisePau1 @VicGovDH It seems you understand the metaphor perfectly well. Also that they solicit reports "no matter how unlikely". If you want to show that the TGA doctor & nurse teams reviewing reports got cases wrong then do it. But, you cannot use the reports as actual likely cause.

@N_J_Bennett @SarahLouisePau1 @VicGovDH Doctors made those reports mate. They concluded it was the vaccine. Deaths are not “chaff”. TGA doesn’t do autopsies so how they know more than the doctor whose patient that is, is also very suspect. Here are 4 deaths from 5-11 year olds in a period of two months from #VAERS. https://t.co/4OLUohXYod

@paulstef @SarahLouisePau1 @VicGovDH TGA explicitly asks for any reports "no matter how unlikely" to be sure nothing is missed by being unreported. They want all the chaff to make sure they don't miss grain.
